result.execSummary:
The defendant Ashley Ann Jaeger was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Ashley Ann Jaeger in court with attorney Joseph Stephen Hoffmann.  Ruth Diane Kressel appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Prev finding or G and a DEJ - agreement that there was a violation. Atty comments admit that there were several violations- did not make $20 payments and was supposed to do 5 hrs of community service, but did not do it at a non profit.. Anger management classes she had to attend. Atty comments proof was not provided in a timely fashion- Did write letter of apology- Made payment on March 27 to pay in full. $10 fine and costs- is the agreement- Atty knows that the admin fees are non refundable and atty would to have the money returned the $140 that def paid after the state made a motion to enter judgment. CT finds def failed to comply with the DEj. Def is convicted of crime of DC- State complied with vic rights- nothing to report- State thinks the fine plus costs is appt. state filed motion on March 6 and set for March 27- atty asking to extend the DEJ as long as def filed proof the counseling was done before the motion was filed- asking the court not require any refund. Atty comments no prior convictions. thinks fine and ct costs is fine. Would like money refunded. Ct orders - 465.15 Ct costs and go to  sheriff office in 7 days for DNA. $25 a month starting in 1 month. Ct comments ct will not order a refund.

Attorney Joseph Stephen Hoffmann in court for Defendant Ashley Ann Jaeger. Prosecuting Atty Kelly J Mcknight appeared for State of Wisconsin. Defendant Ashley Ann Jaeger appeared by phone means. State contents DEJ violated. Atty Hoffmann not contending that violation occured asks for sentencing hearing. Atty Hoffmann comments on payment made to DA asks for $ to be returned, DA has declined, position is that it should be returned. DAP  Sentencing hearing scheduled for May 5, 2017 at 08:30 am.
req to appear by phone - ok per Judge
